39Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I think it's worth moving the clippy::unnecessary_mut_passed lint into rustc because it's a very basic coding mistake:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![allow(unused_variables)]\r\nfn foo(x: &u32) {}\r\nfn bar(a: &[u32]) {}\r\nfn spam(a: &[u32; 10]) {}\r\nfn main() {\r\n    foo(&mut 10);\r\n    let mut a = [0_u32; 10];\r\n    bar(&mut a[..]);\r\n    spam(&mut a);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSee also, for further improvements:\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust-clippy/issues/5546", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/83409/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/83409/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}